ğŸ§© Advanced Array Methods

ğŸ”„ map()

Creates a **new array**.

```js
let nums = [1, 2, 3];
let squared = nums.map(n => n * n);
```

---

ğŸ” filter()

Returns elements that match a condition.

```js
let even = nums.filter(n => n % 2 === 0);
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âœ… reduce()

Reduces array to a single value.

```js
let sum = nums.reduce((total, n) => total + n, 0);
```

---

ğŸ” find()

Returns first matching element.

```js
nums.find(n => n > 2);
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¢ indexOf()

```js
